<tr><td class='diff-marker'>−</td><td class='diff-deletedline'><div>You can get <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">both </del>by {{k|B}}utchering creatures. <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">For </del>[[<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">components#sinew|sinews</del>]] <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">try </del>with <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">mammals </del>(like <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">most </del>[[<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Enemies#Forest_animals|forest animals</del>]]) and other vertebrates. <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">For </del>[[<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">components#plant_fibre|plant fibres</del>]] <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">butcher any </del>[[Enemies#Plants_.26_fungi|plant-like <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">creature</del>]], such as triffids (particularly [[enemies#<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">vinebeast</del>|<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">vinebeasts</del>]]) and <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">fungaloids</del>.</div></td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div>You can get <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">them all </ins>by <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">[[Butcher|</ins>{{k|B}}utchering creatures<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">]], or from {{k|e}}[[Foraging|foraging]] [[underbrush]]</ins>. <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">To be able to butcher you'll need a knife-like tool in your inventory ([[pocket knife]], [[steak knife]], [[combat knife]], etc - check the </ins>[[<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">tools</ins>]] <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">page for any item </ins>with <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">a &quot;butchering&quot; quality). The more butchering quality, the faster you butcher, so a [[hunting knife]] or [[butcher knife]] are your best bet among the most common &quot;knife&quot; tools, followed by the [[steak knife]] or [[combat knife]].</ins>(<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">But something </ins>like <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">a </ins>[[<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Broadsword</ins>]] <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">works too.</ins>)</div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div> </div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">* '''[[Sinew]]''' and '''[[bones]]''': Butcher mammals </ins>and other vertebrates <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">(check the creatures with the BONES flag in the [[enemies]] page for a complete list)</ins>.</div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">* '''</ins>[[<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Plant fibre</ins>]]<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">''': Butcher </ins>[[Enemies#Plants_.26_fungi|plant-like <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">creatures</ins>]], such as triffids (particularly <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">[[vinebeast]]s) and [[fungaloid]]s, or processing some [[Swamp]] plants.</ins></div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">* '''[[Fur pelt]]s''': Butcher a furry creature (check the creatures with the FUR flag in the </ins>[[enemies<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">]] page for a complete list).</ins></div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">* '''Foraging''': {{k|e}}xamine shrubs in forests to find various objects.</ins></div></td></tr>
