<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">=== {{incharacter|Where can I get leather patches, rags and other components?}} ===</ins></div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">* '''[[Rag]]s''': Cut any item made of cotton (like a pair of [[jeans]] or a [[sheet]]). To cut it you need to {{k|a}}ctivate a knife-like tool in your inventory ([[pocket knife]], [[steak knife]], [[combat knife]], etc - check the [http://cdda-trunk.chezzo.com/qualities/CUT item browser] for any item with a &quot;cutting&quot; quality), select {{k|1}} to cut-up fabric and then choose the item in your inventory you want to cut. For [[t-shirt]]s and [[tank top]]s you can [[Crafting</ins>#<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Disassembling_items|disassemble]] them instead (via {{k|(}}). Using the {{k|b}}utcher menu you can also cut up or dissassemble item on the ground, if you have the correct tools.</ins></div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div> </div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">* '''[[Leather patch]]es''': You have the easy way and the hard way. The easy way is to cut leather items following the process mentioned above (items like [[purse]]s, [[sneakers]], [[leather jacket]]s, [[leather pants]] and [[leather gloves]], etc. Check the [[clothing]] page for a complete list). The hard way is by {{k|B}}utchering, and tanning the resulting skin, from creatures with a thick skin (like [[giant frog]]s), or apply a knife to a fur pelt.</ins></div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div> </div></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div><ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">* '''[[Kevlar plate]]s''': Obtained by cutting up kevlar items (i.e [[Kevlar vest|Kevlar vests]], [[Army helmet|Army helmets]], [[Tactical dump pouch</ins>|<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">tactical dump pouches</ins>]] <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">etc.</ins>)<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">. The most common source is probably [[Combat boots|combat boots]]. Turnout gear is another common source of kevlar, and can be found in large quantities in firetrucks </ins>and <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">at fire stations</ins>.</div></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td></tr>
